name: Firestone Tires
directions: Parking lot in front of Winn-Dixie shopping center. Bathroom is directly in front of you  (back wall) as you enter the front door of the store.

name: Biology Building
directions: - 6th Floor, room 601B, Far end of the Hall- 8th Floor, room across from 807, Far end of the Hall

name: LeConte Hall (History)
directions: Enter the West Entrance of the building and head straight down the hall. The bathroom will be n your left.
comment: This bathroom has more than one stall, but a lock on the main door.

name: Women's Studies (Benson Building)
directions: Women's Studies is a very small building. Just ask the desk assistant and they'll point you in the right direction. They're very nice.

name: Physics Building
directions: - 1st (ground) floor, Room 111, Women's Room - 1st (ground) floor, Room 112, Men's Room
comment: Room 111 has no lock for some strange reason!

name: Physics Building
directions: - 2nd (main) floor, Room 228-A, Faculty Restroom- 3rd floor, Room 305-I, Faculty Restroom

name: Chemistry Building
directions: - 2nd Floor, room 249, inside Dr. J. Stickney's Lab. Enter through stairwell door under the Chem Annex.-3rd Floor, room 300, inside Campus Science Stores, head straight back- 4th Floor, room 430, the Chem Auditorium
comment: Avoid going into the Chem Auditorium if there's a class going on.

name: Tate Student Center
directions: Take the Elevator to floor 2. The bathroom is room 204 to the left when you come out of the elevator.

name: University of Georgia Physics Building
comment: The Physics Building is closed on normal University schedule. Getting in on the weekends especially will be difficult.

name: Hugh Hodgson School of Music (UGA)
directions: Two single-stall gendered restrooms are located on the second floor, near the Dancz Center for New Music. They are most easily accessed from the north entrance on the second floor.
comment: Public building hours during the school year: M-F, 7AM-11PM; Sat, 8AM-8PM; Sun, 10AM-11PM. Hours are shorter during the summer, and the building is closed on home football Saturdays.

name: Candler Hall, University of Georgia
directions: bathrooms on the 2nd and 3rd floors
comment: building open 8-5 M-F

name: Starbucks Coffee
directions: directly across from the cash registers
comment: it might seem awkward, but they're single stall locking, and the verizon store next door sends their customers there all the time to use our bathroom, so it's not out of the ordinary at all.

name: Starbucks Coffee
directions: Gender-neutral bathroom on the first floor in the hallway
comment: requires the key from the counter (ask politely if you can't find it at the bar); usually there's only a \"buy something\" policy during football season, or if you're rude.

name: Espresso Royale Caffe
directions: The bathrooms are located at the back of the main area past the register and to the left of the microwave.
comment: The bathrooms are marked \"Manly,\" and \"Ladylike.\"

name: Pita Pit
comment: the owner is a transphobic jerk, and i wouldn't brave an attempt during bar rush, but they're single-stall locking bathrooms, and the employees usually couldn't care less, but would probably prefer it if you refrain from doing coke lines off the sink.

name: University Health Center
directions: From the entrance, walk past the receptionist (don't be afraid, the receptionist won't stop you) and turn right at the elevator. The bathrooms are located here on every floor.
comment: These bathrooms are NOT single stall locking. They are single stall in a larger bathroom. The Health Center is open 8 AM-8 PM Monday-Friday, and 10 AM-5 PM Saturday-Sunday.

name: Memorial hall
comment: Most of the building closes at 5, but you can probably still get in until 9 or 10.

name: Tate Center Movie Theater
directions: On the third floor of the main Tate building is the movie theater. When you enter the movie theater, continue straight ahead until you find the bathrooms.
comment: If it's during the day (not during a showing), you may be able to sneak in, or get someone to let you in.

name: Thomas Street Sculpture Building
comment: The buildings are locked at night (total lock-down is usually between 7 and 9), but if you poke around you can usually find a way in at least to the sculpture studio bathrooms after hours.

name: Wal Lart
directions: At the back of the store
comment: You can go right into the family restroom and do your business. If you are the kind of person that rather do their business in peace without anybody knowing what you are doing this is the place to do it. Nice and clean and a kiddie size toilet too!!!!

name: Rio Bravo Mexican Cafe'
directions: Straight back, behind the sales counter.

name: Target
directions: Next to Pharmacy
comment: Locking gender neutral restroom. I believe this restroom was made in accordance with DC's law...

name: Starbucks North & Wells
directions: There are two stalls. No gender on door.

name: lake mead cruises
street: boat dock just inside lake mead nra
directions: off us 93 in lake mead nra $5 fee per car to enter park
comment: many unisex restrooms in the boathouse and on the boat itself

name: claim jumper
directions: family restroom down the restroom hallway

name: brio tuscan grille
directions: unisex restroom in the restroom area, door says famiglia on it

comment: The Rainbow Center is open year round from 9AM to 9PM Monday through Thursday9AM to Midnight, FridayClosed, Saturday2PM to 9PM, Sunday

directions: entry on calhoun side

directions: on right entering dining area

name: los charros
directions: back of dining area

name: Save-On-Foods

name: Center on Halsted
directions: Restrooms on 2nd and 3rd floors of this LGBTQ community center. Second floor facility located in main corridor, opposite community meeting rooms. Third floor facility located near recreation hall.
comment: Center on Halsted is open 7 days/week. See www.centeronhalsted.org for more information.

name: Center oh Halsted
directions: Gendered Restrooms on 1st, 2nd, and 3rd floors Also one gender neutral restroom on both the second and third floor of this LGBTQ community center. Second floor facility located in main corridor, opposite community meeting rooms. Third floor facility located near recreation hall.
comment: Center on Halsted is open 7 days/week.

name: public bathrooms
directions: Public, single stall restrooms in the beach parkinglot.

name: Olympic Coffee House
directions: It is in the strip mall shopping center next to a computer store a few shops down from the Subway Shop. Fred Meyer is the key business in this shopping center.
comment: Suite 119, this is a VERY friendly place cool music, great prices great coffee of the day, board games etc. Very relaxed atmosphere, equality is prevalent.

name: OLD SCHOOL PIZZA
directions: Downtown Olympia Washington,, free parking in the lot next to the building....

name: Book Revue Bookstore
directions: You have to ask at the sales desk for key for bathroom as does everyone.

name: Locus on Main
directions: Back of Restaurant
comment: Single-stall bathrooms, they are officially marked with the classical mars/venus symbols, but in such a way that the symbols are deliberately hard to see, and the staff encourages first-come-first-serve to both of them.Staff are cool with trans and queer people (the lesbian bartender makes wicked mojitos).

name: Drake Tower
directions: In the hallway to the left of the elevators. Ring the office for entry, key 1000 on the security box.

name: Anoka Ramsey Community College
comment: The bathrooms are either close to the men's or women's rooms and it is a single stall where you lock the door.

name: Traditions cafe and Worls Folk Art
Starbucks
comment: Most Starbucks have single stalls, if not all of them.

name: Far East
directions: In the back, behind the counter. Ask server for directions.

name: Cafe Vita
directions: recently changed to gender neutral

name: Planned Parenthood of Connecticut
directions: Bathrooms in the health center are gender neutral.  In Administration building, gender neutral bathrooms are available on first and third floors.
comment: Due to safety concerns and anti-choice wackos, you must have an appointment or be participating in a training in order to enter the building.  Once you're there, though, you can pee to your heart's content!

name: Orca Books
directions: Straight back from the entrance.
comment: It very explicitly says that bathrooms are for customers only, but it's a bookstore, so it's pretty easy to pretend like you're browsing if you have a few minutes to spare.  They probably won't bug you about it unless you run in, use the bathroom, then run right out.

name: Cold Stone
directions: Right there in the back.

name: Paul & Elizabeth's Restaurant
directions: This is a restaurant on the main floor of Thorne's Marketplace. Look for the big green awning that says Thorne's on it if you're unfamiliar with Northampton.
comment: This is a vegetarian restaurant, so you need to buy something.  They also keep the key at the counter so you need to ask for it.  They're not the friendliest people in the world, but that seems to apply to everyone no matter the sexuality or gender identity.  However, their food is delicious and they're on of the only vegetarian restaurants in Northampton.

name: Faces
directions: You can't miss it.  It's right in the middle of main street.
comment: They're open until 10 most nights, and would never notice if you didn't buy anything.

name: Starbucks
directions: It's in the back of the store, on the left.  They leave the key in the door so you don't have to ask anyone working there for it.
comment: Really LGBT-friendly space.

name: wal-mart supercenter
directions: rear of store behind shoes

name: rave motion picture theater

comment: ticket holders only

name: Whitman College Music Building
directions: Second floor, near the elevatorNeed a WID card to get into the building at night and during academic breaks.

name: Bay Cove Early Intervention/Small Wonders Nursery School
directions: All restrooms in building are accessible single-person restrooms with signs that say 'either.'
comment: Since this is a program that serves kids, you obviously can't walk in off the street and wander around the program. But if you're looking for an early childhood program as a parent or potential employee, this gives some idea as to their mindset.

name: Salt Palace Convention Center
directions: Just north of the South entrance on W. 200 are the entrances to the Ballrooms, to the right of the entry. There are three bathrooms. The Women\\'s is nearest the south entrance, the Men\\'s is closest to the Ballroom entrance. The Unisex bathroom is next to the Men\\'s, and is labeled, \\'Accessible Unisex Bathroom\\' on the sign over the bathrooms.
comment: Depending on the event going on at the Salt Palace, access may be restricted. Some events check ID, others do not.
